-- Argentine peso hits record low of 14 per dollar on black market
-- By Walter Bianchi
-- Thu Aug 21, 2014 02:31PM EDT
-- None



BUENOS AIRES, Aug 21 (Reuters) - Argentina's peso currency fell 3.2 percent to a new record low of 14.0 per dollar on the black market on Thursday, traders said, in reaction to the latest escalation in the country's battle with holdout creditors.

